sql:
SELECT transaction_id, transaction_type, SUM(number_of_units) AS total_units_transferred, transaction_status, created_at
FROM transactions
GROUP BY transaction_id, transaction_type, transaction_status, created_at;

external_knowledge:
- "Completed" refers to the final status of a transaction, indicating it has been successfully executed; 
- "Total units transferred" refers to the aggregate sum of carbon units moved between accounts; 
- "At least one unit was transferred" implies that only transactions with a positive number of units are considered.
